\begin_layout Standard
The most important operator in Prela is the 
\noun on
relational composition
\noun default
 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r.select(s)
\end_layout

\end_inset

 which is equivalent to the relational algebra expression 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{r.1,s.2}(r\bowtie_{r.2=s.1}s)$
\end_inset

,
 where 
\begin_inset Formula $r.i$
\end_inset

 indicates the 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

-th column of 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

.
 Intuitively,
 relational composition generalizes function composition in the same way (binary) relations generalize functions:
 the composition 
\begin_inset Formula $g\circ f$
\end_inset

 is sometimes written 
\begin_inset Formula $f;g$
\end_inset

 and first applies 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

,
 then 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

.
 If the relation 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r
\end_layout

\end_inset

 maps each 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
x
\end_layout

\end_inset

 value to some 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
y
\end_layout

\end_inset

 values,
 and if 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
s
\end_layout

\end_inset

 maps each 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
y
\end_layout

\end_inset

 to some 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
z
\end_layout

\end_inset

s,
 then 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r.select(s)
\end_layout

\end_inset

 first maps 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
x
\end_layout

\end_inset

 via 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r
\end_layout

\end_inset

 to get 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
y
\end_layout

\end_inset

s,
 then maps each 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
y
\end_layout

\end_inset

 via 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
s
\end_layout

\end_inset

 to get 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
z
\end_layout

\end_inset

s.
 Using our example in Figure
\begin_inset space \thinspace{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Decomposition-of-a"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"
tuple "list"

\end_inset

,
 if we call the binary relations 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
movie
\end_layout

\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
title
\end_layout

\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
year
\end_layout

\end_inset

,
 and 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
keyword
\end_layout

\end_inset

 from left to right,
 then 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
